[
  {
    "text": "The world can be a toxic place.",
    "start": 4.334,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "No one knows this more\nthan women and girls,",
    "start": 7.671,
    "duration": 2.627
  },
  {
    "text": "cis and trans,",
    "start": 10.298,
    "duration": 1.794
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as nonbinary people.",
    "start": 12.092,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "I am a journalist",
    "start": 14.636,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "with 30 years’ experience",
    "start": 16.346,
    "duration": 1.335
  },
  {
    "text": "reporting on the injustices women\nand others face around the world.",
    "start": 17.681,
    "duration": 3.169
  },
  {
    "text": "I’m a co-founder of the Man Up Campaign",
    "start": 21.851,
    "duration": 3.212
  },
  {
    "text": "to energize youth activism\nagainst sexual and gender-based violence.",
    "start": 25.063,
    "duration": 4.171
  },
  {
    "text": "I’m a father to two daughters,",
    "start": 30.068,
    "duration": 2.336
  },
  {
    "text": "I’m a life partner to a woman",
    "start": 32.404,
    "duration": 2.502
  },
  {
    "text": "and I’m a Black man in America.",
    "start": 34.906,
    "duration": 1.502
  },
  {
    "text": "Holding these identities --",
    "start": 37.826,
    "duration": 1.376
  },
  {
    "text": "and many more --",
    "start": 39.202,
    "duration": 2.711
  },
  {
    "text": "I say this call to action to you",
    "start": 41.913,
    "duration": 2.711
  },
  {
    "text": "with the deepest sincerity",
    "start": 44.624,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "and utmost gravity.",
    "start": 45.917,
    "duration": 1.251
  },
  {
    "text": "It is time for a gender reckoning,",
    "start": 48.878,
    "duration": 4.004
  },
  {
    "text": "beginning with men authentically\nconfronting our internal selves",
    "start": 52.882,
    "duration": 5.047
  },
  {
    "text": "and each other",
    "start": 57.929,
    "duration": 1.335
  },
  {
    "text": "through the toxicity within us.",
    "start": 59.264,
    "duration": 1.501
  },
  {
    "text": "Against the backdrop\nof Black Lives Matter protest,",
    "start": 61.975,
    "duration": 3.879
  },
  {
    "text": "cries for a racial reckoning\nhave echoed throughout the world,",
    "start": 65.854,
    "duration": 3.962
  },
  {
    "text": "at times seeming premature",
    "start": 69.816,
    "duration": 2.002
  },
  {
    "text": "and largely misunderstood.",
    "start": 71.818,
    "duration": 1.251
  },
  {
    "text": "I believe a true gender reckoning\nmust be the center",
    "start": 74.404,
    "duration": 4.171
  },
  {
    "text": "of any transformative movement\nfor social justice and equity.",
    "start": 78.575,
    "duration": 2.919
  },
  {
    "text": "But what is a reckoning?",
    "start": 82.746,
    "duration": 1.167
  },
  {
    "text": "Dictionaries say it means\nto resolve a bill or a debt.",
    "start": 84.914,
    "duration": 3.421
  },
  {
    "text": "In other words, to settle an account.",
    "start": 89.294,
    "duration": 2.044
  },
  {
    "text": "In the case of women and girls,",
    "start": 92.756,
    "duration": 1.918
  },
  {
    "text": "what is the debt owed to them?",
    "start": 94.674,
    "duration": 1.46
  },
  {
    "text": "Who’s to pay it?",
    "start": 96.968,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "And how?",
    "start": 99.179,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "The consequences of male toxicity\ncontinue building",
    "start": 100.93,
    "duration": 3.379
  },
  {
    "text": "the debt to which I refer,",
    "start": 104.309,
    "duration": 1.376
  },
  {
    "text": "including, among others,",
    "start": 105.685,
    "duration": 1.543
  },
  {
    "text": "a gender wealth gap most affecting women\nwho care for their families",
    "start": 107.228,
    "duration": 4.296
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as act as the primary\nincome generators",
    "start": 111.524,
    "duration": 2.628
  },
  {
    "text": "for their households.",
    "start": 114.152,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "Today, in the United States and abroad,",
    "start": 116.279,
    "duration": 4.129
  },
  {
    "text": "threats to reproductive justice endanger\nthe lives and hard-fought rights of women",
    "start": 120.408,
    "duration": 6.257
  },
  {
    "text": "in regards to their bodily,\nsexual and gender autonomy,",
    "start": 126.665,
    "duration": 4.921
  },
  {
    "text": "impacting the most disenfranchised\ncommunity in society.",
    "start": 131.586,
    "duration": 2.628
  },
  {
    "text": "And violence against women,",
    "start": 135.298,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "in all of its forms,",
    "start": 136.591,
    "duration": 1.794
  },
  {
    "text": "still represents\nan existential challenge,",
    "start": 138.385,
    "duration": 2.335
  },
  {
    "text": "as we’ve seen domestic violence\nrise in the pandemic,",
    "start": 140.72,
    "duration": 2.711
  },
  {
    "text": "as people were confined to their homes,",
    "start": 143.431,
    "duration": 2.211
  },
  {
    "text": "we’ve seen online and public\nharassment flourish,",
    "start": 145.642,
    "duration": 3.003
  },
  {
    "text": "unabated.",
    "start": 148.645,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "The sexual trafficking,",
    "start": 150.313,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "prostitution,",
    "start": 152.273,
    "duration": 1.085
  },
  {
    "text": "exploitation of women and girls\nthrives as ever before.",
    "start": 153.358,
    "duration": 4.046
  },
  {
    "text": "From where does this toxicity come",
    "start": 159.114,
    "duration": 2.043
  },
  {
    "text": "and why?",
    "start": 161.157,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "Men are not endangered,",
    "start": 162.325,
    "duration": 2.378
  },
  {
    "text": "we’re not under assault,",
    "start": 164.703,
    "duration": 1.751
  },
  {
    "text": "we’re not being unfairly maligned.",
    "start": 166.454,
    "duration": 1.669
  },
  {
    "text": "In fact, it’s men, or certain types of\nmasculinity, that are the issue.",
    "start": 168.707,
    "duration": 4.129
  },
  {
    "text": "To be clear,",
    "start": 174.796,
    "duration": 2.002
  },
  {
    "text": "being a man does not make me",
    "start": 176.798,
    "duration": 2.92
  },
  {
    "text": "or anyone else who identifies as a man",
    "start": 179.718,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "inherently toxic.",
    "start": 181.553,
    "duration": 1.042
  },
  {
    "text": "But masculinity,",
    "start": 184.18,
    "duration": 1.252
  },
  {
    "text": "in certain forms,",
    "start": 185.432,
    "duration": 1.751
  },
  {
    "text": "can harm women,",
    "start": 187.183,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "girls,",
    "start": 188.893,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "nonbinary people",
    "start": 190.186,
    "duration": 1.502
  },
  {
    "text": "and men",
    "start": 191.688,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "through violence,",
    "start": 192.981,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "dominating power",
    "start": 194.816,
    "duration": 1.335
  },
  {
    "text": "and control.",
    "start": 196.151,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "So how do we address this?",
    "start": 197.944,
    "duration": 1.251
  },
  {
    "text": "How can we men step up",
    "start": 201.239,
    "duration": 2.794
  },
  {
    "text": "and better support our daughters,",
    "start": 204.033,
    "duration": 2.128
  },
  {
    "text": "our sisters,",
    "start": 206.161,
    "duration": 1.668
  },
  {
    "text": "our female partners,",
    "start": 207.829,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "our colleagues, neighbors and friends?",
    "start": 209.539,
    "duration": 2.085
  },
  {
    "text": "Through what means can men both instigate\nand lead a gender reckoning?",
    "start": 213.501,
    "duration": 4.588
  },
  {
    "text": "First, we must tell the truth.",
    "start": 221.05,
    "duration": 2.712
  },
  {
    "text": "We must tell the truth.",
    "start": 225.513,
    "duration": 2.086
  },
  {
    "text": "Men grow into this world\nbecoming who we’re expected to be",
    "start": 228.892,
    "duration": 3.795
  },
  {
    "text": "or who we think we’re expected to be",
    "start": 232.687,
    "duration": 2.002
  },
  {
    "text": "based on cultural expectations",
    "start": 234.689,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "and inaccurate historical narratives.",
    "start": 236.816,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "As a short, chubby Black kid\nwearing glasses growing up,",
    "start": 240.028,
    "duration": 3.837
  },
  {
    "text": "I was repeatedly told I cried too much.",
    "start": 243.865,
    "duration": 3.045
  },
  {
    "text": "I’m too emotional,",
    "start": 247.494,
    "duration": 1.501
  },
  {
    "text": "too soft.",
    "start": 248.995,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "It was ingrained in me\nthat to prove my masculinity",
    "start": 250.872,
    "duration": 3.587
  },
  {
    "text": "I had to display physical prowess --",
    "start": 254.459,
    "duration": 1.918
  },
  {
    "text": "intimidation.",
    "start": 256.377,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "Because of that indoctrination,",
    "start": 258.171,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "as an adult,",
    "start": 260.131,
    "duration": 2.002
  },
  {
    "text": "I refused to seek help\nfacing escalating health challenges,",
    "start": 262.133,
    "duration": 3.796
  },
  {
    "text": "including high blood pressure",
    "start": 265.929,
    "duration": 1.877
  },
  {
    "text": "and mental trauma.",
    "start": 267.806,
    "duration": 1.209
  },
  {
    "text": "The archetype of manhood nearly killed me.",
    "start": 269.849,
    "duration": 2.962
  },
  {
    "text": "I say that as a survivor\nof two heart attacks,",
    "start": 274.646,
    "duration": 5.13
  },
  {
    "text": "four years on dialysis",
    "start": 279.776,
    "duration": 1.877
  },
  {
    "text": "and a kidney transplant ...",
    "start": 281.653,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "aside from the physical risk\nI put myself into",
    "start": 283.78,
    "duration": 2.377
  },
  {
    "text": "covering wars around the world.",
    "start": 286.157,
    "duration": 1.502
  },
  {
    "text": "The injury we do to ourselves",
    "start": 289.828,
    "duration": 2.794
  },
  {
    "text": "and the women around us",
    "start": 292.622,
    "duration": 2.085
  },
  {
    "text": "comes from fear of losing control,",
    "start": 294.707,
    "duration": 4.255
  },
  {
    "text": "of lack of external affirmation",
    "start": 298.962,
    "duration": 3.044
  },
  {
    "text": "and simply out of shame.",
    "start": 302.006,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "Manhood is a spectrum of identities.",
    "start": 304.926,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "There is no one way to be a man.",
    "start": 307.679,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "And sometimes, discovering one’s true\nmanhood is a lifelong journey.",
    "start": 310.807,
    "duration": 3.545
  },
  {
    "text": "Secondly,",
    "start": 316.98,
    "duration": 2.252
  },
  {
    "text": "we must be consistent.",
    "start": 319.232,
    "duration": 1.251
  },
  {
    "text": "Men,",
    "start": 322.026,
    "duration": 1.752
  },
  {
    "text": "especially men of color,",
    "start": 323.778,
    "duration": 2.461
  },
  {
    "text": "cannot expect women to stand up for us,",
    "start": 326.239,
    "duration": 4.171
  },
  {
    "text": "with us in the face\nof systemic oppressions",
    "start": 330.41,
    "duration": 3.67
  },
  {
    "text": "when too often we do not\ndo the same for them.",
    "start": 334.08,
    "duration": 2.628
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause and cheers)",
    "start": 338.001,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 339.002,
    "duration": 5.255
  },
  {
    "text": "The Black Lives Matter\nmovement for example,",
    "start": 345.592,
    "duration": 2.711
  },
  {
    "text": "founded, named and led\nby queer women of color,",
    "start": 348.303,
    "duration": 5.88
  },
  {
    "text": "still centers Black men’s well-being",
    "start": 354.183,
    "duration": 4.588
  },
  {
    "text": "in the face of unfair policing",
    "start": 358.771,
    "duration": 2.419
  },
  {
    "text": "and criminal justice systems.",
    "start": 361.19,
    "duration": 1.419
  },
  {
    "text": "And where’s the reciprocal\nsupport from those men,",
    "start": 363.693,
    "duration": 2.669
  },
  {
    "text": "including myself,",
    "start": 366.362,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "in addressing intercommunity violence\nagainst women of color,",
    "start": 368.197,
    "duration": 4.463
  },
  {
    "text": "maternal health inequity,",
    "start": 372.66,
    "duration": 1.961
  },
  {
    "text": "economic disparity?",
    "start": 374.621,
    "duration": 1.042
  },
  {
    "text": "How and where do men show up for women?",
    "start": 376.623,
    "duration": 2.46
  },
  {
    "text": "I wonder ...",
    "start": 380.96,
    "duration": 2.378
  },
  {
    "text": "how many men stood with women\non the steps of the US Supreme Court",
    "start": 383.338,
    "duration": 4.296
  },
  {
    "text": "as they fought for reproductive rights?",
    "start": 387.634,
    "duration": 1.876
  },
  {
    "text": "How many men should have been there?",
    "start": 390.595,
    "duration": 1.752
  },
  {
    "text": "Finally, there can be no reckoning\nwithout accountability.",
    "start": 393.306,
    "duration": 4.463
  },
  {
    "text": "There can be no reckoning\nwithout accountability.",
    "start": 399.437,
    "duration": 4.087
  },
  {
    "text": "Men who commit acts of violence against\nwomen must be held accountable",
    "start": 405.526,
    "duration": 4.713
  },
  {
    "text": "by formal systems of justice",
    "start": 410.239,
    "duration": 2.67
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as other men.",
    "start": 412.909,
    "duration": 1.251
  },
  {
    "text": "Silence in the face of misogynistic\nbehavior and language is complicity.",
    "start": 416.329,
    "duration": 4.546
  },
  {
    "text": "We men need to break free from the pack,",
    "start": 421.668,
    "duration": 4.212
  },
  {
    "text": "take concrete actions to stop violence,",
    "start": 425.88,
    "duration": 3.754
  },
  {
    "text": "create safety",
    "start": 429.634,
    "duration": 1.209
  },
  {
    "text": "and build equity.",
    "start": 430.843,
    "duration": 1.043
  },
  {
    "text": "And most importantly,",
    "start": 433.012,
    "duration": 1.877
  },
  {
    "text": "say something.",
    "start": 434.889,
    "duration": 1.21
  },
  {
    "text": "To be sure,",
    "start": 437.225,
    "duration": 2.169
  },
  {
    "text": "bold men around us are actively working\nto disrupt the narrative of male toxicity.",
    "start": 439.394,
    "duration": 4.879
  },
  {
    "text": "After the 2010 earthquake in Haiti,",
    "start": 446.734,
    "duration": 2.503
  },
  {
    "text": "a local organization,",
    "start": 449.237,
    "duration": 1.418
  },
  {
    "text": "KOFAVIV,",
    "start": 450.655,
    "duration": 1.543
  },
  {
    "text": "invited men to be defenders of women\nand girls in displacement camps,",
    "start": 452.198,
    "duration": 4.63
  },
  {
    "text": "women and girls who were\nat risk of sexual assault.",
    "start": 456.828,
    "duration": 2.419
  },
  {
    "text": "Scores of men answered the call",
    "start": 460.456,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "and can continue to do so today.",
    "start": 462.291,
    "duration": 1.794
  },
  {
    "text": "In New York City,",
    "start": 464.919,
    "duration": 1.335
  },
  {
    "text": "CONNECT NYC,",
    "start": 466.254,
    "duration": 1.626
  },
  {
    "text": "led by a Black man,",
    "start": 467.88,
    "duration": 1.877
  },
  {
    "text": "actively engages community partners\nacross civil society",
    "start": 469.757,
    "duration": 3.17
  },
  {
    "text": "to address family violence.",
    "start": 472.927,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "And in a profession not known generally\nfor its advocacy against gender violence,",
    "start": 475.054,
    "duration": 5.631
  },
  {
    "text": "a professional player\nfor the Washington Football Team",
    "start": 480.685,
    "duration": 2.669
  },
  {
    "text": "has become an unabashed advocate",
    "start": 483.354,
    "duration": 2.002
  },
  {
    "text": "for men to learn",
    "start": 485.356,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "and actively change behaviors\nregarding sexual and physical violence.",
    "start": 486.941,
    "duration": 4.004
  },
  {
    "text": "There is hope;",
    "start": 492.488,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "there is light.",
    "start": 493.489,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "Men around the world\nare putting in the work",
    "start": 495.783,
    "duration": 2.211
  },
  {
    "text": "to catalyze a true gender reckoning.",
    "start": 497.994,
    "duration": 2.294
  },
  {
    "text": "But far more are needed.",
    "start": 501.539,
    "duration": 1.168
  },
  {
    "text": "What I want to say to you today is this.",
    "start": 503.916,
    "duration": 1.919
  },
  {
    "text": "Too many of us --",
    "start": 507.545,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "too many men --",
    "start": 508.546,
    "duration": 1.627
  },
  {
    "text": "don’t understand",
    "start": 510.173,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "that equity,",
    "start": 512.133,
    "duration": 1.793
  },
  {
    "text": "justice,",
    "start": 513.926,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "inclusivity,",
    "start": 515.219,
    "duration": 1.544
  },
  {
    "text": "safety for women, girls\nand nonbinary people",
    "start": 516.763,
    "duration": 4.587
  },
  {
    "text": "serves and saves us all.",
    "start": 521.35,
    "duration": 2.128
  },
  {
    "text": "Broken masculinity harms societies,",
    "start": 524.687,
    "duration": 2.92
  },
  {
    "text": "full stop.",
    "start": 527.607,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "When we men reckon with that truth,",
    "start": 529.233,
    "duration": 2.628
  },
  {
    "text": "we will finally find our shared humanity.",
    "start": 531.861,
    "duration": 2.002
  },
  {
    "text": "Women,",
    "start": 535.281,
    "duration": 1.21
  },
  {
    "text": "girls,",
    "start": 536.491,
    "duration": 1.418
  },
  {
    "text": "nonbinary people,",
    "start": 537.909,
    "duration": 1.751
  },
  {
    "text": "men",
    "start": 539.66,
    "duration": 1.043
  },
  {
    "text": "standing together on equal footing",
    "start": 540.703,
    "duration": 2.544
  },
  {
    "text": "with mutual respect",
    "start": 543.247,
    "duration": 1.252
  },
  {
    "text": "in safe environments",
    "start": 544.499,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
